<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.85-3.2 mm long (mean = 2.94 mm; n = 4); 2.29-2.38
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the pronotum appearing basic (type 2) when viewed dorsally, anterior margin serrate; declivital surface shagreened, dull, opaque; declivity glabrous; declivital interstriae 1-3 multiseriate granulate, granules strongly confused; and declivital interstriae 2-4 flat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
